comments: Collins (ATL) establishes himself in the legal screening position in the path of Avdija (WAS) and some contact occurs as the defending players switch the on-ball screen.
Wright (ATL) briefly places and removes a marginal hand from the front of Neto (WAS). The marginal contact has not impact on Neto's SQBR.
Bogdanovic (ATL) legally contests Avdija (WAS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Collins (ATL) moves into Avdija's (WAS) body to establish a post position in the paint. Some marginal contact occurs but Avdija's position is not compromised by the contact.

Replay review of the out of bounds called on Bogdanovic (ATL) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Bogdanovic is last to make contact with the ball prior to it going out of bounds.
Collins (ATL) places an arm around the back of Kuzma (WAS) and slides it off as the ball is inbounded with no impact to Kuzma's FOM.
Kuzma (WAS) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Young (ATL) and some marginal contact occurs that does not inhibit Young's defensive play.

Collins (ATL) makes contact with Neto's (WAS) right arm as he attempts to bring his arm to a vertical position. The contact to Neto's arm impacts his control of the ball during the driving shot attempt.

Caldwell-Pope (WAS) legally contests the perimeter shot attempt by Young (ATL), who lands safely on the ground before turning his body and some marginal contact occurs with the former that does not impact the play.

Kuzma (WAS) briefly places a forearm to the back of Collins' (ATL) neck but the marginal contact has no impact on Collins' rebounding opportunity. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Hunter (ATL) moves into Kuzma's (WAS) path and delivers body contact that affects his SQBR.  The illegal contact occurs before Kuzma gathers the ball and is in his shooting motion.
Avdija (WAS) is not in the path of Wright (ATL) when he extends his right arm out into his path and grazes Wright's shoulder. The marginal contact has no impact on the trailing defender's play.
Wright (ATL) legally contests the perimeter jump shot attempt from Caldwell-Pope (WAS).
Bogdanovic (ATL) places his arms to the front of Avdija (WAS) and extends slightly as he disengages but the contact is only marginal.
Neto (WAS) moves laterally into Young's (ATL) path and Young is able to move through the marginal contact.
Avdija (WAS) makes lower body contact with Young (ATL) as he steps to the rim after the gather and the contact impacts the driving shot attempt.
Hunter (ATL) has two hands to the sides of Kuzma (WAS) away from the ball but Hunter is not holding the offensive player and the marginal contact has no impact on Kuzma's FOM.
Neto (WAS) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
